John Charles Makurdii The Benue State Commissioner for Health, Dr Emmanuel Ikwulono, is dead According to the Government House sources, the commissioner  died as a result of complications from surgery  for an undisclosed hospital. “He attended the last State Executive Council meeting last week and subsequently went for the surgery. READ ALSO: Abandoned bodies litter Ondo mortuary as corpses turn skeleton “His death came as a rude shock this evening”, the government house source said. Ikwulono was sworn in as Commissioner for Health and Human Services  in August 5,2020, to replace Dr Sunday Ongbabo who voluntarily resigned his appointment a week earlier. Copyright PUNCH.
